cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a framework for human pose estimation using top-down feedback, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The framework involves a self-correcting model that progressively changes an initial solution, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The paper also introduces the concept of Iterative Error Feedback (IEF), which is a novel algorithmic technique that could be of interest to the artificial intelligence community (cs.AI). The task of articulated pose estimation involves modeling the structure of human bodies, which could be relevant to the robotics community (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the MPII and LSP benchmarks, which are commonly used in multimedia research (cs.MM).
